              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Stacks consisted of sandwiched KBr pellets, each",
                "followed by monitor foils ofAl (0.0679 g/cm2) and",
                "Cu (0.118 and 0.0500 g/cm2 for protons < 40MeV).",
                "Pellets (0.628 and 0.314g, 10mm radius, for",
                "protons <40 MeV) were prepared from KBr salt powder",
                " (purity 99.5%) pressed into tablets and sandwiched",
                "between two thin (0.00461 g/cm2) Al foils."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "HPGE"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The radioactivity of the reaction residuals",
                "in each sample was determined non-destructively by",
                "gamma-ray spectrometry using an intrinsic HPGe detector",
                "with a thin Be window, a relative efficiency of ~25%",
                "and a resolution of ~2.1keV FWHM at 1.33MeV."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DECAY-DATA": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Selenium radioisotopes were identified using decay",
                "data by Firestone (1996)"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ERR-ANALYS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": "ERR-T",
                "minimum_value": null,
                "maximum_value": null,
                "correlation_property": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " The overall uncertainty in the calculated",
                "cross-section values was taken as the square root of",
                "the sum of the squares of the following individual",
                "uncertainties:",
                "  - foil thickness (1%),",
                "  - peak fitting (1%),",
                "  - counting geometry (1%),",
                "  - detector efficiency (5%),",
                "  - decay correction (1%),",
                "  - beam current integration (6%),",
                " summing up to a statistical subtotal of 8.1%.",
                " Furthermore, beam loss correction and counting",
                " statistics (both variable) were taken into account.",
                " The statistical total, thus, amounts to a maximum",
                " of 39%."
              ]
            }
          ],
